<seg id=1> The International Court at the Hague convicted three defendants of war crimes against Bosnians and Serbs, but their high-ranking army commanders were not sentenced guilty. </seg>
<seg id=2> The International Court convicted that Muslim Feralichi of Bosnia need not to be responsible for his troops' violence committed against the Serb prisoners and criminals of war in the Chelibich POW Camp in 1992. </seg>
<seg id=3> Other three defendants were sentenced to fixed-term imprisonment for the function they performed in what the people called the terrorist rule in the POW camp. </seg>
